article.headline: UC Irvine 63, UC Riverside 37
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Darren Fells had 11 points and eight rebounds to lead UC Irvine to a 63-37 win over UC Riverside Wednesday night. The victory gives the Anteaters (14-11, 10-3) a guaranteed top-two finish in the Big West and an automatic berth into the semifinals of the conference tournament in March. Irvine has pulled within percentage points of Big West leader Pacific as the conference schedule winds down. The loss drops UC Riverside (3-19, 3-8) into sole possession of last place. The 37-point total was the lowest UC Irvine has allowed a Division I school since a 57-37 win at St. Mary's on January 3, 2001. With the game tied 12-12 with 8:14 to play in the first half, Irvine went on a 23-0 run that featured four 3-pointers. The Anteaters went into halftime with a 35-12 lead. UC Riverside shot 18.5 percent in the first half, and never threatened in the second half. Steve Williams led the Highlanders with 10 points.
